value.value: 肢芽の幅広化
increased anterior-posterior width of the mesenchymal outgrowth on the lateral trunk of the embryo that develops into the limbs
肢芽の矮小化
reduced size of the mesenchymal outgrowth on the lateral trunk of the embryo that develops into the limbs
アブミ骨底の形態異常
any structural anomaly of transient  developing limb structure that forms by expansion of the distal end of the limb paddle and will give rise to the pedal appendages (e.g. hand, foot, paw)

label.value: abnormal cochlear hair cell inter-stereocilial links morphology

value.value: 蝸牛有毛細胞不動毛間結合の異常

https://w3id.org/babelon/source_value.value: abnormal cochlear hair cell inter-stereocilial links morphology

value.value: any structural anomaly in the morphologically and biochemically distinct link types that extend between the stereocilia of cochlear hair bundles; link types can be distinguished by their relative sensitivities to treatment with calcium chelators and the protease subtilisin; in the mature mouse cochlea, tip links and horizontal top connectors are the only inter-stereocilial links associated with the hair bundle; ankle links and transient lateral links are both prominent features of developing auditory hair bundles

label.value: abnormal cochlear hair bundle tip links morphology

value.value: 蝸牛不動毛先端糸の異常

https://w3id.org/babelon/source_value.value: abnormal cochlear hair bundle tip links morphology

value.value: any structural anomaly in single, three-stranded interrow filaments that extend obliquely from the tip of one stereocilium to the lateral side of an adjacent taller stereocilium; in the mouse, tip links are already detectable prenatally and persist throughout life; tips links are thought to gate the mechanotransducer channel, are lost from the cell surface after exposure to either calcium chelator BAPTA or lanthanum, and resist degradation by the protease subtilisin

label.value: abnormal cochlear hair bundle horizontal top connectors morphology

value.value: 蝸牛不動毛先端結合の異常

https://w3id.org/babelon/source_value.value: abnormal cochlear hair bundle horizontal top connectors morphology

value.value: any structural anomaly in the inter-stereocilial links that connect the top of a shorter stereocilium to an adjacent longer stereocilium at a short distance below the tip links; the appearance of horizontal top connectors, which persist into adulthood, occurs concomitant with this loss of ankle links; top connectors are essentially unaffected by treatment with subtilisin and EGTA

label.value: abnormal cochlear hair bundle transient lateral links morphology

value.value: 蝸牛不動毛束一過性側方リンクの異常

https://w3id.org/babelon/source_value.value: abnormal cochlear hair bundle transient lateral links morphology

value.value: any structural anomaly in the fine lateral links that interconnect stereocilia at prenatal stages; transient lateral links diminish at early postnatal stages when ankle links appear at the base of stereocilia, and are essentially unaffected by treatment with subtilisin and EGTA

label.value: abnormal cochlear hair bundle ankle links morphology

value.value: 蝸牛不動毛束アンクルリンクの異常

https://w3id.org/babelon/source_value.value: abnormal cochlear hair bundle ankle links morphology

value.value: any structural anomaly in the long, single-stranded filaments that form a dense web or mesh around the base of cochlear hair bundles just above the region in which the stereocilia begin to taper down; in the mouse, ankle links are only a transient feature of the developing cochlear hair bundles, present predominantly from P2 though P9, but are absent by P12; ankle links are disrupted by treatment of hair cells with EGTA and subtilisin but not by La3+ and elastase

label.value: absent cochlear hair bundle ankle links

value.value: 蝸牛不動毛束アンクルリンクの欠損

https://w3id.org/babelon/source_value.value: absent cochlear hair bundle ankle links

value.value: absence of the long, single-stranded filaments that form a dense web or mesh around the base of cochlear hair bundles just above the region in which the stereocilia begin to taper down

label.value: abnormal vestibular hair bundle inter-stereocilial links

value.value: 前庭不動毛束間リンクの異常

https://w3id.org/babelon/source_value.value: abnormal vestibular hair bundle inter-stereocilial links

value.value: any structural anomaly in the morphologically and biochemically distinct link types that extend between the stereocilia of vestibular hair bundles

label.value: abnormal vestibular hair bundle shaft connectors

value.value: 前庭不動毛束軸結合の異常

https://w3id.org/babelon/source_value.value: abnormal vestibular hair bundle shaft connectors

value.value: any structural anomaly in the links that connect the shafts of neighboring stereocilia in vestibular hair bundles; each shaft connector is composed of a ruthenium red-reactive, electron-dense particle that is connected to the plasma membrane by several fine strands of variable length

label.value: absent vestibular hair bundle shaft connectors

value.value: 前庭不動毛束軸結合の欠如

https://w3id.org/babelon/source_value.value: absent vestibular hair bundle shaft connectors

value.value: absence of the inter-stereocilial links that connect the shafts of neighboring stereocilia in vestibular hair bundles
柱細胞の変性
degeneration or loss of the supporting cells that form the inner and outer walls of the tunnel in the organ of Corti

label.value: decreased cellular sensitivity to X-ray irradiation

value.value: 細胞のX線照射感受性低下

https://w3id.org/babelon/source_value.value: decreased cellular sensitivity to X-ray irradiation

value.value: decreased incidence of cell death following exposure to X-ray irradiation
前庭有毛細胞の発達異常
atypical initial production, differentiation, migration or maturation of hair cells in the sensory epithelium of the maculae and cristae of the membranous labyrinth of the inner ear
蝸牛有毛細胞の発達異常
atypical initial production, differentiation, migration or maturation of the sensory epithelial cells of the cochlea
ダイテルス細胞の欠如
absence of the supporting cells of the spiral organ which are attached to the basement membrane and receive the hair cells between their free extremities
蓋膜の肥大化
increased size of the overlaying membrane of cochlear duct, an extracellular matrix of the inner ear that contacts the stereocilia bundles of specialized sensory hair cells
下顎骨の矮小化
reduced size of the lower bony framework of the mouth where the inferior teeth are held
下顎骨長の増加
increased length of the lower bony framework of the mouth where the inferior teeth are held
下顎骨鉤状突起の形態異常

any structural anomaly of the thin, flattened, triangular eminence that arises from the upper surface of the mandibular ramus (perpendicular portion); includes the attachment site to the temporal muscle
下顎骨関節突起の形態異常

any structural anomaly of the round bump of bone and constricted neck portion that arises from the upper surface of the mandibular ramus (perpendicular portion) and articulates with the articular disk of the temporomandibular joint
下顎角の形態異常
any structural anomaly of the portion of the mandible where the body of the mandible (horizontal portion) and the rami (perpendicular portions) meet; these normally unite nearly at right angles

label.value: increased susceptibility to noise-induced hearing loss

value.value: 騒音性聴覚消失に対する感受性上昇

https://w3id.org/babelon/source_value.value: increased susceptibility to noise-induced hearing loss

value.value: greater than normal reduction in hearing sensitivity following exposure to acute noise that is injurious to the cochlea
蝸牛基底膜の異常

any structural anomaly in the continuous basement membrane found within the membranous labyrinth of the cochlea, known to extend from the limbus, down to the inner sulcus, across the basilar membrane, up to the external sulcus to the spiral prominence and radiating into the spiral ligament ensheathing the root cell processes
椎弓の形態異常

any structural anomaly of the dorsal bony and/or cartilaginous part of a vertebra, consisting of a pair of pedicles, a pair of laminae, and seven processes (four articular processes, two transverse processes, and one spinous process)
椎骨横突起の異常

any structural anomaly of the bony protrusions on either side of the arch of a vertebrae at the point where the lamina joins the pedicle, between the superior and inferior articular processes; muscles and ligaments attach to these processes
椎骨棘突起の異常
any structural anomaly of the dorsal projection of the vertebral arch that projects backward and downward from the junction of the laminae, and serves for the attachment of muscles and ligaments
椎骨関節突起の異常
any structural anomaly of the bilateral flat projections that arise from the junctions of the pedicles and laminae
椎弓の欠如
loss of the dorsal part of a vertebra, consisting of a pair of pedicles, a pair of laminae, and seven processes (four articular processes, two transverse processes, and one spinous process)
椎弓根の形態異常
any structural anomaly of the two short, thick processes, which project backward, one on either side, from the upper part of the body to the laminae
椎弓板の形態異常
any structural anomaly of two broad plates directed dorsomedially from the pedicles; these fuse at the dorsal midline, and complete the dorsal wall of the vertebral foramen
椎骨棘突起の欠如
missing the dorsal projection of the vertebral arch that projects backward and downward from the junction of the laminae, and serves for the attachment of muscles and ligaments
頚部環椎の形態異常
any structural anomaly of the first (topmost, C1) cervical vertebra which supports the globe of the head
頚部軸椎の形態異常
any structural anomaly of the second cervical vertebra (C2) which forms the pivot upon which the first cervical (atlas, C1) vertebra rotates
椎骨の融合
the union of one or more vertebrae into a single structure
椎骨の矮小化
reduced size of the bony segments of the spinal column

label.value: increased susceptibility to ototoxicity-induced hearing loss

value.value: 中毒性聴覚損失に対する感受性上昇

https://w3id.org/babelon/source_value.value: increased susceptibility to ototoxicity-induced hearing loss

value.value: greater than normal reduction in hearing sensitivity following exposure to an ototoxic compound, such as aminoglycoside-induced hearing loss mediated via a glutamate excitotoxic process
椎体の融合
improper union of the main cylindrical portion of adjacent vertebra ventral to the vertebral canal
椎弓の融合
improper union of the dorsal part of adjacent vertebra
尾椎骨の形質転換
homeotic transformation of any caudal vertebrae to adopt the fate of another vertebrae

definition.value: There are usually 27-30 caudal vertebrae present in rodents and only 3-5 fused caudal vertebrae in human.

value.value: 頚椎骨の形質転換
homeotic transformation of any cervical vertebrae to adopt the fate of another vertebrae
腰椎骨の形質転換
homeotic transformation of any lumbar vertebrae to adopt the fate of another vertebrae
仙椎骨の形質転換
homeotic transformation of any sacral vertebrae to adopt the fate of another vertebrae
胸椎骨の形質転換
homeotic transformation of any thoracic vertebrae to adopt the fate of another vertebrae
尾椎の融合
the union of one or more caudal vertebrae into a single structure in species where this does not normally occur

definition.value: There are usually 27-30 caudal vertebrae present in rodents and only 3-5 fused caudal vertebrae in human.

value.value: 頚椎の融合
the union of one or more cervical vertebrae into a single structure
腰椎の融合
the union of one or more lumbar vertebrae into a single structure
仙椎の融合
the union of one or more sacral vertebrae into a single structure in species where this does not normally occur

definition.value: In humans, vertebrae S1-S5 are normally fused in maturity, with no intervertebral discs. In rodents, these vertebrae remain distinct in adulthood.

value.value: 胸椎の融合
the union of one or more thoracic vertebrae into a single structure
